        {
          "SUBENT": {
            "N1": "B0114002",
            "N2": 20011220,
            "alteration_flag": " ",
            "transmission_identification": "0000"
          },
          "BIB": {
            "N1": 7,
            "N2": 0
          },
          "REACTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "82-PB-208(3-LI-6,X)84-PO-211-M,IND,SIG,,,EXP",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "82-PB-208(3-LI-6,X)84-PO-211-M,IND,SIG,,,EXP",
                    "field": {
                      "reaction": "82-PB-208(3-LI-6,X)84-PO-211-M",
                      "target": "82-PB-208",
                      "projectile": "3-LI-6",
                      "process": "X",
                      "product": "84-PO-211-M",
                      "quantity": "IND,SIG",
                      "data_type": "EXP",
                      "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                      "quantity_236": "IND,SIG"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The Cross Sections are Strongly Connected to the",
                "Break-Up of the Li-6 Projectile Followed by Capture",
                "Of the Beam-Veclocity Alpha-Particle - \"Internal",
                "Break-Up Reaction\".  At 156 MeV the Internal Break-Up",
                "Contribution was Experimentally Separated from That",
                "Part of the Cross Section Due to Compound/Precompound",
                "Reactions. This Part is Less Than 10%",
                "For Lower Energies It was Assumed That this Part",
                "Plays a Minor Role, Too."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "RAD-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "flag": null,
                "nuclide": "84-PO-211-M",
                "radiation_type": [
                  "A"
                ]
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "In Addition to the Decay Energy the Alpha-Peaks were",
                "Identified in a Separate Run Via the Half-Life by",
                "Measuring in a Multispectrum Scaling Procedure."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DECAY-DATA": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "flag": null,
                "nuclide": "84-PO-211-M",
                "half-life": {
                  "value": 25.5,
                  "unit": "SEC"
                },
                "radiation": [
                  {
                    "radiation_type": [
                      "A"
                    ],
                    "energy": [
                      7270.0
                    ],
                    "intensity": 0.91
                  },
                  {
                    "radiation_type": [
                      "A"
                    ],
                    "energy": [
                      8880.0
                    ],
                    "intensity": 0.07
                  }
                ]
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "High Spin Isomer (J=25/2+). The Isomer is not Product",
                "Of at-211 and Rn-215 Radioactive Decay."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Pb-208, Thickness 0.15 Mg/Cm**2, Evaporated onto",
                "20 Micro G/Cm**2 C-Foil. The Thickness was Determined",
                "By Measuring the Energy Loss of Am-241 Alpha-Particles."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "SITA",
                "EDEG",
                "BCINT",
                "REC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The Initial Projectile Energy of 156 MeV was Stepwise",
                "Degraded by be-Sheets. The Energy Loss of Li-6 was",
                "Calculated Using Extrapolations of the Energy Loss",
                "Relation of L.C.Northcliffe and R.F.Schilling, Nucl.",
                "Data Tables A7 (1970).",
                "The Recoils have Been Catched in Carbon Foils of",
                "Various Thicknesses. The Catcher Foils were Mounted on",
                "A Pneumatic Driven Slider Transporting the Activity",
                "Out of the Beam to the Measuring Position.",
                "Each Measuring Cycle Consisted of",
                "The Irradiating Period, the Recording Period and the",
                "Transport Period, Forth and Back.",
                "The Beam Current was 15 Nanoampere, Typically."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "STATUS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Numerical Values of the Data were Obtained by",
                "The Author."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FLAG": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                1.0
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "This Value was Erroneously Quoted As 85 Mb",
                "Instead of 85 Microbarn in the Publication."
              ]
            }
          ],
